 drops, and then everyonr that would use the item other than you is excluded from teh group.<br /><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Scenario (b) of your post proves my point. I am not going to roll on plate, chain or leather. Thus, the group you describe gives half of the members an exclusive shot at an item (if it drops) and two of the members a 50/50 shot at an item. <br /><br />Under your description, who gets what under the NBG system depends on what drops. A necro doesn't need plate anymore than a pally needs silk. And so if the members need those items, necro - silk and pally - plate, why would I roll on plate that I don't need when someone else present does. If I roll on plate because no one in the group needs it, then it is not a NBG loot system being used. <br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />The problem on the ornate example is for the Cleric and warrior that already have ornate or better. They ahve no chance at getting anything.<br /><br />It's that 2/3 of the group have a chance to get an item, and 1/3 has no chance of getting an item... even worse, that same 1/3 will NEVER get a chance in a NBG pickup group... Unlike the melee camp vs. caster camp, they will NEVER get a chance.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Please explain if I misunderstand something you've stated.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />hopefully i just did =P</span id="msg"></font></td>
