                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The Need before Greed system was created under the goal of making the game a better place for everyone.  It was NOT created to be a fair system of loot - that came later down the line because people wanted to make NGB seem like the ideal system so as to promote their own welfares.<br /><br />The NGB system was created not to be fair, but to be a system of equality.  That's exactly correct, Laeelin - it is a welfare system.  The basic principles of NBG are simple: the poor gets richer, the rich do not.  It is built under the preconception that the rich does not need to become richer (e.g. if yo'ure in elemental gear, the best you can make out with in a group is twink gear, and people would rather not gear up other people's twinks when they can gear up other people's mains).  It draws support from the ideal that if everyone did NGB then everyone would be generally better off because you'll get what you need faster.<br /><br />NGB follows the Communist line of thought: give to society as according to your ability, take from it as according to your need.  Is this a bad system of thought? Depends on your political alignment, I guess (and whether you believed deeply in the anti-Communist sentiments of American history), but there is no denying that it is not going to be "fair" system.  The goal of NGB and Communism is universal equality, not equality of opportunity, which is what "fairness" is defined as nowadays.<br /><br />Whether you support NGB or not depends on you.  It is certainly abuseable and in no way as fair as just doing /random 1 1000 whenever something drops, but on the other hand, I could remember back to the time when parchment drops were awarded to melees in certain groups and the outcry that created.  Frankly, people will believe what it is to their advantage to believe, and nothing you or I say is going to change that.  We are all biased in RL and in EQ and that's that.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><hr noshade size="1"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Etadanik the Redeemed</span></font></td>
