n had come along, which i wanted. I was offered a deal to trade my chipper and my money for it. I made it a point to find the leader of the raid and ask him whether or not i should return the chipper and put it up for /random. I was told to keep it but its the thought that counts.<br /><br />The other thing that has fell out of practice with NBG is swapping. In my guild, if a nice item upgrade drops, and im wearing a dropable peice in that slot, i may be asked to pass my item down to someone when i get this upgrade. It's all supposed to be to better the guild and get us to the point of doing better things.<br /><br />Now i wouldnt expect swapping in a XP group, but there are things more important than money. <br /><br />If someone was to call NBG on an item and then sell it i would make it a point to not group with them again, simple as that.</span id="msg"></font></td>
